Modelling The Number Of Feeds For Bird Chicks

Short Masters Statistics Fundamentals Project

Published on January 16, 2022

•

8 minutes

•

1536 words

Context: As part of my Statistical Fundamentals module I wrote a report on some Bird Chick Feeding Data (fictional), analysing which factors affect the amount of food chicks from this species receive. I was disappointment in my work for this project because I felt I could have done better given more time. I was awarded a letter grade of A for this project which translated to 75% (presumably to mitigate against grade inflation). My work in this project, alongside my coursework grades, was a contributing factor in the lecturers decision to approach me about a PhD opportunity with him. All analysis in this project was conducted using R.
